race.comment: CHELSEA (1) was restrained through the early stages then ran on nicely without threatening first-up over 1200m at this track. Lightly raced four-year-old who will relish the extra ground today. Back in good shape and looks the one to beat. CRUDO (9) is the danger after a nice effort over 1280m at Muswellbrook last time out when facing the starter for only the second time. Settled handy on that occasion and tried hard but found one better despite pulling up 3/5 lame. Sure to give a good account. O'BRITZELLE (10) has been in the betting but failed to trouble the judge in her two runs to date. Might be worth one more chance with this step up in distance. EPIC STATEMENT (8) disappointed as favourite when resuming over this course and distance 15 days ago. Capable of a lot better. CRASHMYPLAYA (3) ran on powerfully here at today's journey last time. Yet to place in ten runs but is heading the right way.
